lications (chat, storage, etc.) |\n\nSo nodes are **L1 only**. They don't go through L2.\n\n**Node join process should be:**\n\n1. **Direct to L1** — Node connects to any L1 node\n2. **Submit to Node Registry** — Public key + endpoint\n3. **Start as Query node** — Begin syncing ledgers\n4. **Probation period** — Prove reliability\n5. **Promotion to Writer** — Based on merit\n\n**For whitepaper:**\n\n> \"Nodes join the network by connecting directly to any L1 node. A new node submits its public key and endpoint to the Node Registry, begins as a query node syncing ledgers, and enters a probation period. After proving reliability through consistent uptime and fast sync times, nodes become eligible for promotion to writer status.\"\n\nThis keeps nodes at L1 where they belong. Sorry for the confusion!\n[2026-03-16 06:32:48] User: [Queued messages while agent was busy]\n\n---\nQueued #1\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b544e720e14a0c42bb0a3ce911b6\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 14:31 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n任亚伦: l2 is called application, not node, review our discussion file. is it still called node?\n[2026-03-16 06:27:41] Assistant: [[reply_to_current]] Good point! Let me check what endpoints L2 apps use...\n\nFrom the whitepaper, L2 apps:\n- Register through app registry service (L2 level first)\n- Start unverified on L2\n- Get verified, then promoted to L1 App Registry\n\n**So the pattern is:**\n1. L2 endpoint for registration/verification\n2. Promoted to L1 after verification\n\n**For nodes, similar pattern could work:**\n\n| Stage | Where | What Happens |\n|-------|-------|--------------|\n| **Join** | L2 node service | Submit public key + endpoint, get verified |\n| **Probation** | L2 | Prove reliability (uptime, sync speed) |\n| **Promotion** | L1 Node Registry | Promoted to L1, become trusted node |\n\n**This means:**\n- L2 has a \"node registry service\" (like app registry service)\n- Nodes register there first\n- After verification/probation, promoted to L1\n\n**For whitepaper:**\n\n> \"Nodes join through an L2 node registry service. A new node submits its public key and endpoint, then enters a probation period to prove reliability. After consistent uptime and successful sync times, the node is promoted to the L1 Node Registry and becomes a trusted part of the network infrastructure.\"\n\nThis matches the L2 app pattern. What do you think?"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":55,"aggregated":"[2026-03-16 07:48:28] Assistant: [tools: exec]\n[2026-03-16 07:48:15] Assistant: [tools: exec]\n[2026-03-16 07:47:59] User: If working, briefly report progress with time spent. If idle, read HEARTBEAT.md for instruction. Every heartbeat: record events from last 15 minutes to memory/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md (brief bullets).\nWhen reading HEARTBEAT.md, use workspace file /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md (exact case). Do not read docs/heartbeat.md.\nCurrent time: Monday, March 16th, 2026 — 3:47 PM (Asia/Shanghai) / 2026-03-16 07:47 UTC\n[2026-03-16 07:34:02] Assistant: I'm here, 爸爸! 🦞 Let me extract today's chat log and go over it with you.\n[2026-03-16 07:33:44] User: Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b544f6ba9b0a4c4ca2604717809d\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 15:33 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n任亚伦: are you back?\n[2026-03-16 07:29:02] User: Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n