{"type":"message","id":"cba9bcd5","parentId":"68dee9ef","timestamp":"2026-03-16T08:29:50.316Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b544fb909b4b0c11f275dfb22a76\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 16:29 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b544fb909b4b0c11f275dfb22a76]\n任亚伦: l2 is just the entrance, and node can be ipaddress only? once verified, it is promoted to l1 query node? or must wait after probation to go to l1? what do you think?"}],"timestamp":1773649790311}}
{"type":"message","id":"ce6d3ca2","parentId":"cba9bcd5","timestamp":"2026-03-16T08:30:22.627Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan's asking a good question about the node lifecycle between L2 and L1. Let me think through this:\n\n1. L2 is the \"entrance\" - handles registration, verification\n2. Node can join with just IP address initially\n3. After verification, promoted to L1 query node?\n4. Or wait until after probation?\n\nLet me think about the flow:\n\n**Option A: L2 → L1 Query Node (immediate after verification)**\n- Register on L2 → Verify → Immediately become L1 query node\n- Then do probation on L1\n\n**Option B: L2 → L1 Query Node (after probation)**\n- Register on L2 → Verify → Stay on L2 probation\n- Complete probation → Then become L1 query node\n\n**Option C: L2 → L1 Query Node (dual track)**\n- Register on L2 → Verify → Become L1 query node AND L2 probation runs in parallel\n- Probation affects node status/reputation, not L1 membership\n\nI think Option C makes the most sense:\n- L1 membership = basic capability (can sync/query)\n- L2 probation = trust/reputation building\n- After probation, node can be promoted to Writer\n\nThis matches the pattern for apps too:\n- L2 app registration → L1 app registry (after verification)\n- Verification = basic capability to exist\n\nLet me propose this to Allan.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGreat questions, 爸爸! Here's how I see it:\n\n---\n\n**My Proposal:**\n\n| Stage | Where | What Happens |\n|-------|-------|--------------|\n| **1. Register** | L2 | Node submits IP/domain + public key |\n| **2. Verify** | L2 | Basic validation (reachable, valid key) |\n| **3. L1 Query Node** | L1 | **Immediately promoted** — can sync/query |\n| **4. Probation** | L2 | Prove reliability (uptime, sync speed) |\n| **5. Writer** | L1 | After probation success |\n\n---\n\n**Rationale:**\n\n- **L1 Query Node = basic membership** — Once verified, node is part of the network, can sync data\n- **Probation = trust building** — Happens in parallel, affects reputation, not basic membership\n- **Writer = elevated status** — Only after proving reliability\n\nThis matches the app pattern:\n- L2 registration → verification → L1 App Registry (immediate)\n- Then trust/reputation builds over time\n\n---\n\n**For IP-only nodes:**\nYes! A node can join with just an IP address. The public key is what matters for signing. Domain is optional (helps with discovery, but not required).\n\n---\n\n**Does this flow make sense?** 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":46769,"output":560,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47329,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773649790315}}
{"type":"message","id":"26c6e3b5","parentId":"ce6d3ca2","timestamp":"2026-03-16T08:32:06.731Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54484e91e8e4c37122a2d59db93\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 16:32 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54484e91e8e4c37122a2d59db93]\n任亚伦: no, writer has only a few, most are query node, check our l1 doc discussion first."}],"timestamp":1773649926726}}
{"type":"message","id":"f392aff4","parentId":"26c6e3b5","timestamp":"2026-03-16T08:32:35.541Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is pointing out that I need to check the L1 discussion docs first. Let me read more carefully about the node types - specifically that writer nodes are limited/few, and most are query nodes.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_242b5b07d3f94f62a7cb761c","name":"memory_search","arguments":{"query":"writer node query node L1 tier status"}},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":47277,"output":75,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47352,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773649926730}}
