{"type":"message","id":"bdcaf68d","parentId":"8b2bc68c","timestamp":"2026-03-16T08:41:04.117Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54486f2fa4b4c2cb84dc5ccc278\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 16:41 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54486f2fa4b4c2cb84dc5ccc278]\n任亚伦: then no probation? if i't on l1 as query. i't already there"}],"timestamp":1773650464112}}
{"type":"message","id":"65911a13","parentId":"bdcaf68d","timestamp":"2026-03-16T08:41:34.698Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is making a good point. If a node is promoted to L1 query node immediately after verification, then there's no probation period at the L1 level. The probation (if any) would be for becoming a WRITER, not for being a query node.\n\nSo the flow should be:\n1. Register on L2\n2. Verify on L2\n3. Promoted to L1 query node (immediately, no probation)\n4. (Optional) Prove merit over time → become writer\n\nThe \"probation\" is only for writer promotion, not for query node status.\n\nLet me confirm this understanding with Allan.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nYou're right, 爸爸! If query node = L1 membership, then there's no probation for being on L1.\n\n**Simplified Flow:**\n\n| Stage | Where | What Happens |\n|-------|-------|--------------|\n| **1. Register** | L2 | Node submits IP + public key |\n| **2. Verify** | L2 | Basic validation (reachable, valid key) |\n| **3. L1 Query Node** | L1 | **Immediately promoted** — no probation |\n| **4. Writer** | L1 | Only after proving merit (long term) |\n\n**So:**\n- Query node = basic membership on L1 (no probation)\n- Writer = elevated status (merit-based, happens over time)\n\n**Probation is only for becoming a writer**, not for being a query node.\n\n---\n\n**Correct?** 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":52574,"output":303,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52877,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773650464115}}
{"type":"message","id":"9fece97e","parentId":"65911a13","timestamp":"2026-03-16T08:43:11.050Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5448672ced04c44573f0eb761c1\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 16:43 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5448672ced04c44573f0eb761c1]\n任亚伦: or maybe after register and verify, it can stay as probation node on l2? then after proven, it then store on l1?"}],"timestamp":1773650591045}}
{"type":"message","id":"38447ac6","parentId":"9fece97e","timestamp":"2026-03-16T08:44:00.772Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is proposing a different flow:\n\n1. Register on L2\n2. Verify on L2\n3. Stay as \"probation node\" on L2 (not on L1 yet)\n4. After proven, then store on L1 as query node\n5. Then later can become writer\n\nSo the node is \"on probation\" at L2 level, not on L1. Only after proving itself does it get stored on L1.\n\nThis makes sense from a design perspective:\n- L1 is the \"trusted\" layer - you don't want unverified nodes stored there\n- L2 is the \"entrance\" - handles verification before promoting to L1\n- Only after proving reliability does the node get stored on L1\n\nThis is cleaner separation:\n- L2: registration, verification, probation\n- L1: trusted nodes only (query nodes, writers)\n\nLet me confirm this understanding with Allan.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nAh, that's a cleaner design! \n\n**Proposed Flow:**\n\n| Stage | Where | What Happens |\n|-------|-------|--------------|\n| **1. Register** | L2 | Node submits IP + public key |\n| **2. Verify** | L2 | Basic validation |\n| **3. Probation Node** | L2 | Prove reliability (uptime, sync) — not on L1 yet |\n| **4. L1 Query Node** | L1 | After proven → stored on L1 ledger |\n| **5. Writer** | L1 | After long-term merit |\n\n**Benefits:**\n- L1 only stores **trusted** nodes (no unverified nodes on the ledger)\n- L2 is the \"entrance\" — handles all verification before L1\n- Clean separation: L2 = entrance/gatekeeper, L1 = trusted storage\n\n---\n\n**This is what you meant by \"L2 is just the entrance\"!** \n\nL2 handles the whole verification process. Only after passing does the node get promoted to L1.\n\n---\n\n**Correct?** 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":52987,"output":412,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53399,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773650591049}}
