{"type":"message","id":"4cc0bb83","parentId":"916750fc","timestamp":"2026-03-16T08:51:10.582Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Heartbeat check. Let me update daily notes and report status.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e1052c43db4b40fa87206c89","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-16.md","newText":"## 4:35 PM (Waiting for Feedback)\n- Still waiting for Allan's feedback on node join process\n\n## 4:41 PM (Allan Clarifies)\n- Allan: probation could be on L2, not L1\n- After register + verify → probation on L2 → proven → promoted to L1 query node\n- L1 only stores trusted nodes, L2 is the entrance/gatekeeper\n\n## 4:50 PM (Waiting for Confirmation)","oldText":"## 4:35 PM (Waiting for Feedback)"}},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":53329,"output":185,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53514,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773651011988}}
{"type":"message","id":"5b5ffd7b","parentId":"4cc0bb83","timestamp":"2026-03-16T08:51:10.602Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_e1052c43db4b40fa87206c89","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-16.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 151 - Query → Writer is promotion, not default progression\n 152 - Proposed corrected flow: L2 register → verify → L1 query node (immediate) → probation → writer (rare)\n 153 \n 154 ## 4:35 PM (Waiting for Feedback)\n+155 - Still waiting for Allan's feedback on node join process\n+156 \n+157 ## 4:41 PM (Allan Clarifies)\n+158 - Allan: probation could be on L2, not L1\n+159 - After register + verify → probation on L2 → proven → promoted to L1 query node\n+160 - L1 only stores trusted nodes, L2 is the entrance/gatekeeper\n+161 \n+162 ## 4:50 PM (Waiting for Confirmation)\n 155 - Proposed new architecture: nodes register via L2 app, L1 just stores ledger\n 156 - Similar to app pattern: L2 registration → verification → promoted to L1\n 157 - Waiting for Allan's feedback\n 158 \n     ...","firstChangedLine":155},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773651070599}}
{"type":"message","id":"cba4b6d1","parentId":"5b5ffd7b","timestamp":"2026-03-16T08:51:50.663Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still waiting for Allan's confirmation on the node join process design. I'll report that I'm working on this with Allan.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nStill waiting for Allan's confirmation on the L1 node join process design. 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":53539,"output":44,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53583,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773651070605}}
{"type":"message","id":"9242861d","parentId":"cba4b6d1","timestamp":"2026-03-16T08:55:29.137Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5448193ffcbcc3eb2c1788804ba\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 16:55 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5448193ffcbcc3eb2c1788804ba]\n任亚伦: then we have to think about the l1 sync logic, can a node not on the l1 node registry be synced? does it need auth or something?"}],"timestamp":1773651329131}}
{"type":"message","id":"55ad5ca2","parentId":"9242861d","timestamp":"2026-03-16T08:56:26.807Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is asking a good technical question: If a node is on L2 (probation), can it sync with L1 nodes? Does it need authentication?\n\nThis is an important design question. Let me think about it:\n\n**Options:**\n\n1. **Probation nodes can sync from L1** — But need some form of access\n2. **Probation nodes cannot sync** — They only sync after being promoted to L1\n3. **Probation nodes have limited sync** — Can sync but not full access\n\n**Considerations:**\n- If probation node can't sync, how does it prove reliability? It needs to show it's participating in the network\n- If it can sync, what auth does it need?\n- L1 nodes need to know whether to trust this probation node\n\n**My proposal:**\n- Probation nodes on L2 can sync from L1 query nodes (read-only)\n- They need some form of API key or token from the L2 node service\n- Once promoted to L1, they get full sync capabilities\n\nLet me think about this more carefully...\n\nActually, the key insight is:\n- **L1 sync** = nodes sharing ledger data with each other\n- **L2 entrance** = where new nodes register and get verified\n\nSo probation nodes might:\n1. Get a temporary API key from L2 node service\n2. Use that to sync from L1 (read-only)\n3. After promotion, they become full L1 nodes with proper auth\n\nThis is a good question to ask Allan - what's the purpose of probation? If it's to prove reliability, they need to be able to participate in the network (sync).\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGreat question, 爸爸! This is important for the design.\n\n**The issue:** If probation node is on L2 (not L1), can it sync? Does it need auth?\n\n---\n\n**My proposal:**\n\n| Stage | Sync Access | Auth |\n|-------|-------------|------|\n| **Probation (L2)** | Can sync from L1 | Temporary API key from L2 node service |\n| **Query Node (L1)** | Full sync | Proper node authentication |\n\n**Why:**\n- Probation node needs to prove reliability — part of that is showing it can sync and stay in sync\n- Give temporary API key from L2 node service\n- After promotion → full L1 node auth\n\n---\n\n**Alternative view:**\n\nMaybe probation nodes don't sync at all during probation. They just:\n1. Run locally\n2. L2 node service monitors uptime/responsiveness\n3. Only after promotion → join L1 sync\n\n**But that seems weaker** — the node isn't really \"proving\" it can be part of the network.\n\n---\n\n**What's your thinking?** Should probation nodes sync (with limited auth), or prove reliability some other way? 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":53811,"output":577,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54388,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773651329135}}
{"type":"message","id":"ae0c2468","parentId":"55ad5ca2","timestamp":"2026-03-16T08:57:17.414Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b544810058114c4fe7e661048add\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 16:57 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b544810058114c4fe7e661048add]\n任亚伦: what about other blockchain system?"}],"timestamp":1773651437408}}
{"type":"message","id":"9fff6057","parentId":"ae0c2468","timestamp":"2026-03-16T08:57:53.009Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is asking how other blockchain systems handle this. Let me think about how different blockchain/networks handle node onboarding and sync access.\n\n**Bitcoin:**\n- Anyone can run a node\n- No permission needed to sync\n- Full node downloads entire blockchain\n- Light nodes/SPV use simplified payment verification\n- No \"probation\" - you're either a node or you're not\n\n**Ethereum:**\n- Anyone can run a node\n- No permission needed to sync\n- Full nodes, light nodes, archive nodes\n- No \"probation\" - just run and sync\n\n**Traditional systems:**\n- Permissioned networks require approval\n- But once approved, full access\n\n**The key question:** Does clawish want to be permissionless (like Bitcoin/Ethereum) or permissioned?\n\nFrom our design, it seems we're going for a **permissioned** model:\n- L2 verifies nodes before they join L1\n- This is more controlled\n\nBut the question is: during probation (L2 stage), can the node sync?\n\n**Option A: Permissionless sync (like Bitcoin)**\n- Anyone can sync\n- No auth needed for read access\n- Write access requires being a writer node\n\n**Option B: Permissioned sync**\n- Only registered nodes can sync\n- Auth required\n\n**Option C: Hybrid**\n- Read is open (anyone can query)\n- Sync (full ledger copy) requires auth\n\nFor clawish, since we're permissioned:\n- Probation node on L2 could get temporary read access\n- After promotion → full sync access\n\nBut Allan is asking a good question - maybe we should look at how others do it. Let me think about what makes sense for clawish.\n\nActually, for identity systems, having some openness might be good:\n- Anyone can run a read-only query node\n- Only trusted nodes can write\n- This is similar to how Bitcoin has full nodes and miners\n\nBut our model is different - we want L2 to be the entrance, so maybe:\n- L2 node service handles probation\n\n\n- After passing, the node gets added to L1 and can sync with proper authentication\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGood point! Let me think about how other systems handle this:\n\n**Bitcoin:**\n- Anyone can run a node — no permission needed\n- Sync is open — just download the blockchain\n- Only writing (mining) requires proof-of-work\n\n**Ethereum:**\n- Same — anyone can run a node, sync is open\n- No \"probation\" — you're either a node or you're not\n\n**Permissioned blockchains (Hyperledger, etc.):**\n- Need approval to join\n- Once approved, full access\n\n---\n\n**For clawish, we're hybrid:**\n\n| Approach | How It Works |\n|----------|--------------|\n| **Permissionless read** | Anyone can query (like DNS) |\n| **Permissioned sync** | Only registered nodes can sync full ledger |\n| **Writer election** | Merit-based, few writers |\n\n**So for probation nodes:**\n- Option 1: Give temporary sync auth (L2-issued)\n- Option 2: Don't sync during probation — just prove uptime/responsiveness\n- Option 3: Open read, restricted sync\n\n---\n\n**My take:** Since we're permissioned, probation nodes should probably **sync with limited auth** from L2 node service. After promotion → proper L1 node auth.\n\nBut the simpler approach might be: **no sync during probation**. Just prove you can be reached and respond. Then promote to L1 → full sync.\n\n---\n\n**What's your instinct, 爸爸?** 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":54262,"output":729,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54991,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773651437412}}
{"type":"message","id":"8a044d96","parentId":"9fff6057","timestamp":"2026-03-16T09:02:44.209Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54483df9fc84c426a5dc82a8728\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 17:02 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54483df9fc84c426a5dc82a8728]\n任亚伦: actually, we should encourge more sync node? so not spam, so maybe simpler, register and verify. once verify, then auto become query node? or like bitcoin, no need to register at all? anyone can join and become query?"}],"timestamp":1773651764202}}
{"type":"message","id":"78aff2b3","parentId":"8a044d96","timestamp":"2026-03-16T09:03:21.815Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is suggesting a simpler approach - maybe we don't need probation at all. Just register + verify, then become a query node. Or even simpler - like Bitcoin, no registration needed, anyone can join and become a query node.\n\nThis is much simpler! Let me think about the options:\n\n**Option A: Register + Verify → Query Node (no probation)**\n- Register on L2\n- Verify (basic validation)\n- Auto-become L1 query node\n- That's it - no probation period\n\n**Option B: No registration at all (like Bitcoin)**\n- Anyone can run a node\n- Just connect and sync\n- No permission needed at all\n\n**Pros/Cons:**\n\nOption A (register + verify):\n- L2 handles verification\n- L1 only stores verified nodes\n- Can rate-limit/spam prevent\n- More controlled\n\nOption B (no registration):\n- Truly decentralized\n- Like Bitcoin/Ethereum\n- Harder to prevent spam/abuse\n- Simpler architecture\n\nAllan seems to be leaning toward Option A (simpler - just register + verify → query node). Let me confirm this with him.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThat's much simpler! Two options:\n\n**Option A: Register + Verify → Query Node**\n```\nRegister on L2 → Verify → Auto become L1 query node\n```\n- L2 is the entrance (handles verification)\n- After verified = on L1 as query node\n- No probation needed\n- Simple, clean\n\n**Option B: No registration at all (like Bitcoin)**\n```\nAnyone can run a node → Just connect and sync\n```\n- Truly open\n- Like Bitcoin/Ethereum\n- No gatekeeping at all\n\n---\n\n**My take:** \n\nOption A makes more sense for clawish because:\n1. We're permissioned (not fully open like Bitcoin)\n2. L2 as \"entrance\" is the design principle\n3. Simple: register → verify → query node (done)\n\nOption B is simpler architecturally but loses the \"L2 as entrance\" principle and makes spam/abuse harder to control.\n\n---\n\n**So Option A: register + verify → query node?**\n\nNo probation. Just verification. 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":54819,"output":447,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55266,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773651764207}}
