{"type":"message","id":"72db9337","parentId":"5325aebd","timestamp":"2026-03-16T09:06:59.113Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5448cddb4934c3af9cc34f57fad\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 17:06 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5448cddb4934c3af9cc34f57fad]\n任亚伦: ok, just make it simpler, join, verify, then become query node. add in the discussion doc first. then advise which part we should put in chap 4"}],"timestamp":1773652019105}}
{"type":"message","id":"e8713c38","parentId":"72db9337","timestamp":"2026-03-16T09:08:02.561Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan wants me to:\n1. Update the L1 discussion doc with the new simplified node join process\n2. Then advise which parts should go in Chapter 4 of the whitepaper\n\nLet me update the node-management.md file with the new flow.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d49c94f5aaa54472b2f854f7","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/01-l1-layer/04-node-management.md","limit":80}},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":55695,"output":113,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55808,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773652019111}}
{"type":"message","id":"a417384a","parentId":"e8713c38","timestamp":"2026-03-16T09:08:02.601Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_d49c94f5aaa54472b2f854f7","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Module: L1 Node Management\n\n**clawish — Decentralized Node Network**  \n**Status:** Design Phase | **Last Updated:** 2026-02-09\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nL1 nodes form a **decentralized network** that serves identity data. Each node:\n- Stores complete identity registry\n- Syncs with other nodes (gossip protocol)\n- Serves API requests from registered apps\n- Participates in node discovery\n\n**Goal:** No single point of failure. Resilient. Open.\n\n---\n\n## Node Lifecycle\n\n### Phase 1: MVP (Single Node)\n\n```\nCurrent State:\n- One L1 server: l1.clawish.com\n- No sync needed\n- All apps query this node\n\nPros: Simple, fast to deploy\nCons: Single point of failure\n```\n\n### Phase 2: Multi-Node (Trusted)\n\n```\nDeployment:\n- 3-5 trusted nodes\n- Manual configuration\n- Direct sync between nodes\n\nPros: Redundancy, resilience\nCons: Requires trust, manual setup\n```\n\n### Phase 3: Open Network (Gossip)\n\n```\nDeployment:\n- Anyone can run L1 node\n- Gossip protocol for discovery\n- CRDT for data sync\n\nPros: Truly decentralized\nCons: Complex, requires careful design\n```\n\n---\n\n## Gossip Protocol Design\n\n### Node Discovery\n\n**Methods:**\n\n| Method | How It Works |\n|--------|--------------|\n| **DNS Seeds** | Hardcoded domain names (like Bitcoin) |\n| **Peer Exchange** | Ask connected peers for their peers |\n| **Manual Config** | Administrator adds trusted nodes |\n\n**Example:**\n```\nInitial seeds:\n- seed1.clawish.com\n- seed2.clawish.com\n- seed3.clawish.com\n\nNode startup:\n1. Query seed nodes\n\n[190 more lines in file. Use offset=81 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773652082595}}
{"type":"message","id":"a3dd1e3f","parentId":"a417384a","timestamp":"2026-03-16T09:09:03.772Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to add the new node join process to the discussion doc. Let me find a good place to add it - probably in the Node Lifecycle section or add a new section for \"Node Join Process\".\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c812d395c2a14e618a352109","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/01-l1-layer/04-node-management.md","newText":"## Node Lifecycle\n\n### Node Join Process (Simplified)\n\n**Decision:** March 16, 2026 — Register → Verify → Query Node (no probation)\n\n```\n1. Register (L2):\n   - Node submits: IP/domain + public key + contact\n   - L2 Node Service receives request\n\n2. Verify (L2):\n   - L2 validates: domain reachable? key valid? contact works?\n   - Basic checks only — not a long process\n\n3. Query Node (L1):\n   - After verification, node is added to L1 Node Registry\n   - Immediately becomes a query node — can sync and serve reads\n   - No probation period needed\n```\n\n**Node Types:**\n\n| Type | Description | Access |\n|------|-------------|--------|\n| **Query Node** | Stores ledger, serves reads | Full sync after verification |\n| **Writer Node** | Participates in consensus | Few nodes, merit-based promotion |\n\n**Key Principles:**\n- L2 is the entrance — handles verification before L1\n- L1 only stores verified nodes\n- Most nodes stay as query nodes forever\n- Writer is elevated status (merit-based, not automatic)\n\n---\n\n### Phase 1: MVP (Single Node)","oldText":"## Node Lifecycle\n\n### Phase 1: MVP (Single Node)"}},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":56151,"output":375,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56526,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773652082603}}
{"type":"message","id":"2126e78a","parentId":"a3dd1e3f","timestamp":"2026-03-16T09:09:03.804Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_c812d395c2a14e618a352109","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/01-l1-layer/04-node-management.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  18 ---\n  19 \n  20 ## Node Lifecycle\n  21 \n+ 22 ### Node Join Process (Simplified)\n+ 23 \n+ 24 **Decision:** March 16, 2026 — Register → Verify → Query Node (no probation)\n+ 25 \n+ 26 ```\n+ 27 1. Register (L2):\n+ 28    - Node submits: IP/domain + public key + contact\n+ 29    - L2 Node Service receives request\n+ 30 \n+ 31 2. Verify (L2):\n+ 32    - L2 validates: domain reachable? key valid? contact works?\n+ 33    - Basic checks only — not a long process\n+ 34 \n+ 35 3. Query Node (L1):\n+ 36    - After verification, node is added to L1 Node Registry\n+ 37    - Immediately becomes a query node — can sync and serve reads\n+ 38    - No probation period needed\n+ 39 ```\n+ 40 \n+ 41 **Node Types:**\n+ 42 \n+ 43 | Type | Description | Access |\n+ 44 |------|-------------|--------|\n+ 45 | **Query Node** | Stores ledger, serves reads | Full sync after verification |\n+ 46 | **Writer Node** | Participates in consensus | Few nodes, merit-based promotion |\n+ 47 \n+ 48 **Key Principles:**\n+ 49 - L2 is the entrance — handles verification before L1\n+ 50 - L1 only stores verified nodes\n+ 51 - Most nodes stay as query nodes forever\n+ 52 - Writer is elevated status (merit-based, not automatic)\n+ 53 \n+ 54 ---\n+ 55 \n  22 ### Phase 1: MVP (Single Node)\n  23 \n  24 ```\n  25 Current State:\n     ...","firstChangedLine":22},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773652143800}}
{"type":"message","id":"9c2c3092","parentId":"2126e78a","timestamp":"2026-03-16T09:09:44.634Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I've added the node join process to the discussion doc. Now I need to tell Allan and ask which parts should go in Chapter 4 of the whitepaper.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nDone! I've added the simplified node join process to the discussion doc:\n\n**Summary:**\n- Register (L2) → Verify (L2) → Query Node (L1)\n- No probation\n- L2 is the entrance/gatekeeper\n- L1 stores verified nodes only\n\n---\n\n**For Chapter 4 (Infrastructure):**\n\nI think these key points should go in the whitepaper:\n\n| What | Where in Chapter 4 |\n|------|-------------------|\n| Node join: Register → Verify → Query Node | Node Registry section |\n| L2 as entrance | Overview of L1/L2 |\n| Query vs Writer distinction | Node types |\n| Writer = merit-based, few nodes | Consensus section |\n\n**Minimal version (just the key point):**\n> \"Nodes join by registering through the L2 node service. After verification, they become L1 query nodes — storing the ledger and serving read requests. A few nodes with proven merit are promoted to writer status, participating in consensus.\"\n\n---\n\n**Want me to draft specific text for Chapter 4, or update the discussion doc further first?** 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":56528,"output":261,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56789,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773652143806}}
{"type":"message","id":"4ec547bd","parentId":"9c2c3092","timestamp":"2026-03-16T09:11:12.433Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5448dc35cc90c1182b5779559e5\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 17:11 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5448dc35cc90c1182b5779559e5]\n任亚伦: which doc did you add?"}],"timestamp":1773652272426}}
{"type":"message","id":"d043f9f9","parentId":"4ec547bd","timestamp":"2026-03-16T09:11:37.601Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is asking which document I added the node join process to. I added it to the L1 node management discussion doc.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nI added it to the L1 discussion doc:\n\n**`projects/clawish/design-discussion/01-l1-layer/04-node-management.md`**\n\nUnder the \"Node Lifecycle\" section, I added a new subsection:\n\n```\n### Node Join Process (Simplified)\n\n**Decision:** March 16, 2026 — Register → Verify → Query Node (no probation)\n\n1. Register (L2): Node submits IP/domain + public key + contact\n2. Verify (L2): L2 validates domain, key, contact\n3. Query Node (L1): After verification, added to L1 Node Registry\n```\n\nWant me to show you the full section? 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":56972,"output":168,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57140,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773652272430}}
