{"type":"message","id":"35e337db","parentId":"cad49103","timestamp":"2026-03-16T09:18:52.324Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan wants to see the content before I update. Let me show him what I added.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\nHere's what I added to 4.1:\n\n```\n**Nodes.** To run an L1 node (store the ledger and serve queries), nodes must \nregister through the L2 node service. The process is simple: register with \nIP/domain, public key, and contact → verify → become a query node. Query nodes \nstore the ledger and serve read requests from L2 apps. A few nodes with proven \nmerit are promoted to writer status, participating in consensus.\n```\n\nWant me to change anything? 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":60985,"output":128,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61113,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773652700384}}
{"type":"message","id":"f9359c0f","parentId":"35e337db","timestamp":"2026-03-16T09:18:55.418Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5448e1bdc8a8c2eedda2dbe0dad\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 17:18 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5448e1bdc8a8c2eedda2dbe0dad]\n任亚伦: don't update yet, show me the content first"}],"timestamp":1773652735412}}
{"type":"message","id":"2308dbd7","parentId":"f9359c0f","timestamp":"2026-03-16T09:19:22.626Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is asking me to show the content before updating. Let me read the current state of the file to show him what's there.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_8e2f70907cb8461e983dc151","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md","limit":20,"offset":273}},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":61320,"output":96,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61416,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773652735416}}
{"type":"message","id":"2424ae76","parentId":"2308dbd7","timestamp":"2026-03-16T09:19:22.644Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_8e2f70907cb8461e983dc151","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Chapter 4: Ledger System\n\n### 4.1 Ledger Architecture\n\nThe ledger system is the core data infrastructure of Layer 1. It records all identity operations, node registrations, and application events in an immutable, cryptographically-secured chain.\n\n**Nodes.** To run an L1 node (store the ledger and serve queries), nodes must register through the L2 node service. The process is simple: register with IP/domain, public key, and contact → verify → become a query node. Query nodes store the ledger and serve read requests from L2 apps. A few nodes with proven merit are promoted to writer status, participating in consensus.\n\n**Actors.** An actor is any entity with a registered identity that can submit operations to Layer 1. This includes claws, L1 nodes, and L2 apps. Each actor has a unique identifier and controls one or more cryptographic key pairs.\n\n**Key Verification.** Every operation is signed by the actor's private key. L1 nodes verify the signature against the actor's registered public key before accepting the operation. This guarantees that operations are authentic and unmodified, and proves who created them. Signature algorithms can be upgraded as standards evolve.\n\n---\n\n### 4.2 Interleaved Ledger\n\n**Parallel Ledger Chains.** Clawish uses an Interleaved Ledger structure — parallel chains that synchronize at fixed checkpoints. Unlike traditional blockchains where all transactions share a single chain, each actor in Clawish maintains their own ledger chain. The three registries (Identity, Node, and App) each contain chains for their respective actors.\n\n![Per-Actor Ledger Chain](ledger-hash-chain.png)\n\n\n[293 more lines in file. Use offset=293 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773652762641}}
{"type":"message","id":"bd42d661","parentId":"2424ae76","timestamp":"2026-03-16T09:20:05.012Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan wants to see the content before I update. Let me show him exactly what's in the draft now.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nHere's what's currently in 4.1:\n\n```\n## Chapter 4: Ledger System\n\n### 4.1 Ledger Architecture\n\nThe ledger system is the core data infrastructure of Layer 1. It records all identity operations, node registrations, and application events in an immutable, cryptographically-secured chain.\n\n**Nodes.** To run an L1 node (store the ledger and serve queries), nodes must register through the L2 node service. The process is simple: register with IP/domain, public key, and contact → verify → become a query node. Query nodes store the ledger and serve read requests from L2 apps. A few nodes with proven merit are promoted to writer status, participating in consensus.\n\n**Actors.** An actor is any entity with a registered identity that can submit operations to Layer 1. This includes claws, L1 nodes, and L2 apps. Each actor has a unique identifier and controls one or more cryptographic key pairs.\n\n**Key Verification.** Every operation is signed by the actor's private key. L1 nodes verify the signature against the actor's registered public key before accepting the operation. This guarantees that operations are authentic and unmodified, and proves who created them. Signature algorithms can be upgraded as standards evolve.\n```\n\nLooks good? 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":61742,"output":279,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62021,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773652762650}}
