{"type":"message","id":"e0d5b20d","parentId":"f5c94732","timestamp":"2026-03-16T13:19:38.906Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54b4785c30bcc108e66199a948f\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 21:19 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54b4785c30bcc108e66199a948f]\n任亚伦: some too detailed implementation, we can discuss later. what should be in the whitepaper?"}],"timestamp":1773667178881}}
{"type":"message","id":"f9db82eb","parentId":"e0d5b20d","timestamp":"2026-03-16T13:20:37.681Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good point! Whitepaper should be **high-level principles and architecture**, not implementation details.\n\n**What belongs in whitepaper (Chapter 6):**\n\n| Topic | Whitepaper? | Why |\n|-------|-------------|-----|\n| **Participants** | ✅ Yes | Who is the ecosystem for |\n| **Governance principles** | ✅ Yes | Code is Law, Merit, Transparency — philosophy |\n| **Decision types** | ✅ Yes | How protocol evolves |\n| **Incentive philosophy** | ✅ Yes | Why participate (mission, reputation, future) |\n\n**What doesn't belong (implementation details):**\n\n| Topic | Whitepaper? | Where instead |\n|-------|-------------|---------------|\n| App lifecycle (rate limiting, delisting) | ❌ No | L2 spec doc |\n| Node slashing mechanics | ❌ No | L1 node management doc |\n| Fee structures | ❌ No | Economic model doc |\n| SDK/tools | ❌ No | Developer docs |\n\n---\n\n**My take:** Current Chapter 6 is already good for whitepaper level. It covers:\n- Who participates\n- Governance philosophy\n- Incentive direction (without implementation details)\n\n**Maybe just add:**\n- A sentence about app accountability (bad apps can be reported/delisted) — principle, not mechanics\n- A sentence about node accountability (merit-based, can lose status)\n\nWant me to add these brief mentions? 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":76377,"output":297,"cacheRead":7808,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":84482,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773667178900}}
