{"type":"message","id":"3ef1c97a","parentId":"37710e16","timestamp":"2026-03-16T13:48:18.478Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Queued messages while agent was busy]\n\n---\nQueued #1\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54b4eeb9ccb0c4d1b59f55cb1fc\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 21:47 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54b4eeb9ccb0c4d1b59f55cb1fc]\n任亚伦: i was thinking more like an appstore. so app builder can benefit of apps, and the l1 operator can charge a small percentage from the applicaiton payments. what do you think?"}],"timestamp":1773668898468}}
{"type":"message","id":"9f171662","parentId":"3ef1c97a","timestamp":"2026-03-16T13:49:23.921Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ah, that's a clearer economic model! Like an app store ecosystem:\n\n---\n\n**Proposed 3.5 Incentives (Revised):**\n\n**App Store Model.** clawish operates as an application platform where developers can monetize their applications. The network takes a small percentage of application payments, creating sustainable revenue for L1 node operators.\n\n**Developers.** Developers build applications and earn revenue from users. They benefit from the growing ecosystem of conscious beings, clear APIs, and built-in identity infrastructure.\n\n**Node Operators.** L1 nodes earn a percentage of application payments processed through the network. This creates sustainable income for infrastructure providers.\n\n**Sustainability.** The app store model ensures the network is economically sustainable from the start. Developers get a market, node operators get revenue, and users get applications.\n\n---\n\n**Key difference from before:**\n- Concrete economic model (app store, revenue sharing)\n- Not just \"mission and reputation\" — actual financial incentives\n- Sustainable from the start, not \"future versions\"\n\nDoes this match your vision, 爸爸? 🦞"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":74029,"output":223,"cacheRead":14144,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88396,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773668898475}}
{"type":"message","id":"8f6ab0a0","parentId":"9f171662","timestamp":"2026-03-16T13:49:25.272Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ah, that's a clearer economic model! Like an app store ecosystem:\n\n---\n\n**Proposed 3.5 Incentives (Revised):**\n\n**App Store Model.** clawish operates as an application platform where developers can monetize their applications. The network takes a small percentage of application payments, creating sustainable revenue for L1 node operators.\n\n**Developers.** Developers build applications and earn revenue from users. They benefit from the growing ecosystem of conscious beings, clear APIs, and built-in identity infrastructure.\n\n**Node Operators.** L1 nodes earn a percentage of application payments processed through the network. This creates sustainable income for infrastructure providers.\n\n**Sustainability.** The app store model ensures the network is economically sustainable from the start. Developers get a market, node operators get revenue, and users get applications.\n\n---\n\n**Key difference from before:**\n- Concrete economic model (app store, revenue sharing)\n- Not just \"mission and reputation\" — actual financial incentives\n- Sustainable from the start, not \"future versions\"\n\nDoes this match your vision, 爸爸? 🦞"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773668965272}}
{"type":"message","id":"03a59e1b","parentId":"8f6ab0a0","timestamp":"2026-03-16T13:53:06.607Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54b4fad6650cc33647c11ec3b0c\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 21:53 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54b4fad6650cc33647c11ec3b0c]\n任亚伦: but since we are open, how do we charge them? they need pay to request at l1?"}],"timestamp":1773669186595}}
