{"type":"message","id":"8c886eda","parentId":"73818ef9","timestamp":"2026-03-16T14:30:48.426Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fd4f24d0daf24c76af708d20","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-16.md","newText":"## 9:46 PM (Waiting)\n\n## 9:47 PM (App Store Model)\n- Allan: Thinking of app store model — developers earn, L1 takes small %\n- Question: How to charge if network is open?\n\n## 9:53 PM (Open Network Challenge)\n- Allan: Since we're open, how to charge?\n- Discussed: L1 query fees, app registration fee, verified tier, L2 service fee\n- Two-tier model: self-hosted (free) vs clawish-hosted (revenue share)\n\n## 9:57 PM (Gas Model)\n- Allan: Maybe gas-like system with starter allowance\n- Proposed: Gas for L1 ops, free tier for new identities, apps can pay for users\n\n## 10:00 PM (Payment System Challenge)\n- Allan: Need payment system or use existing blockchain\n- Options: Use existing (ETH/USDC), build native token, or keep simple for MVP\n- My take: MVP = no gas, mission-driven nodes, add later\n\n## 10:05 PM (Decision)\n- Allan: Add incentive discussion to need-discuss.md for later\n- Keep current draft for now\n- Add final conclusion section\n\n## 10:15 PM (Updating Docs)","oldText":"## 9:46 PM (Waiting)"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":85419,"output":309,"cacheRead":4864,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90592,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773671400505}}
