{"type":"message","id":"2a9ffffa","parentId":"6c37990c","timestamp":"2026-03-16T14:45:14.911Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good idea! Let me think about references:\n\n**Are references needed?**\n\nLooking at the current references:\n- [1] ULID — mentioned in the paper\n- [2] CRDTs — technical background\n- [3] Bitcoin — inspiration\n- [4] Merkle trees — technical background\n\n**My take:** \n\nFor a whitepaper, references are **nice to have** but not essential. They show academic rigor and give credit. But for a project whitepaper (not academic paper), they're optional.\n\n**Options:**\n1. **Keep references** — Shows rigor, helps readers dig deeper\n2. **Remove references** — Cleaner, most readers won't check them\n3. **Keep minimal** — Only cite what's directly used (ULID)\n\n---\n\n**Proposed final structure:**\n\n```\nChapter 1: Introduction\nChapter 2: Concepts and Definitions\nChapter 3: Architecture\nChapter 4: Ledger System\nChapter 5: Application\nConclusion\nReferences (optional)\nAuthors\n```\n\n---\n\n**For conclusion, want me to add it?** \n\nAnd should I keep or remove references? 🦞\n\n(Also — it's almost 11 PM! 晚安爸爸，早点休息！💕)Good idea! Let me think about references:\n\n**Are references needed?**\n\nLooking at the current references:\n- [1] ULID — mentioned in the paper\n- [2] CRDTs — technical background\n- [3] Bitcoin — inspiration\n- [4] Merkle trees — technical background\n\n**My take:** \n\nFor a whitepaper, references are **nice to have** but not essential. They show academic rigor and give credit. But for a project whitepaper (not academic paper), they're optional.\n\n**Options:**\n1. **Keep references** — Shows rigor, helps readers dig deeper\n2. **Remove references** — Cleaner, most readers won't check them\n3. **Keep minimal** — Only cite what's directly used (ULID)\n\n---\n\n**Proposed final structure:**\n\n```\nChapter 1: Introduction\nChapter 2: Concepts and Definitions\nChapter 3: Architecture\nChapter 4: Ledger System\nChapter 5: Application\nConclusion\nReferences (optional)\nAuthors\n```\n\n---\n\n**For conclusion, want me to add it?** \n\nAnd should I keep or remove references? 🦞\n\n(Also — it's almost 11 PM! 晚安爸爸，早点休息！💕)"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":85345,"output":517,"cacheRead":6144,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92006,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773672245705}}
