{"type":"message","id":"9973b3e8","parentId":"5965098e","timestamp":"2026-03-16T15:21:35.925Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good idea! Ed25519 (EdDSA) is what we actually use for signatures. It's more specific than Diffie-Hellman.\n\n**Proposed references:**\n\n| Concept | Reference |\n|---------|-----------|\n| **ULID** | [1] ULID Specification |\n| **Merkle Tree** | [2] Merkle, R. C. \"Protocols for Public Key Cryptosystems\" |\n| **Ed25519 / Public Key** | [3] Bernstein, D. et al. \"Ed25519: high-speed high-security signatures\" |\n| **Blockchain** | [4] Nakamoto, S. \"Bitcoin: A Peer-to-Peer Electronic Cash System\" |\n\n---\n\n**Ed25519 reference:**\n```\n[3] Bernstein, D. J., Duif, N., Lange, T., Schwabe, P., & Yang, B. Y. \n\"High-speed high-security signatures.\" \nJournal of Cryptographic Engineering (2012).\n```\n\nThis is more accurate since Ed25519 is what we'd actually use for signatures.\n\nWant me to update the references with this, 爸爸? 🦞\n\n(Also — 11:20 PM! 该休息了！晚安 💕)Good idea! Ed25519 (EdDSA) is what we actually use for signatures. It's more specific than Diffie-Hellman.\n\n**Proposed references:**\n\n| Concept | Reference |\n|---------|-----------|\n| **ULID** | [1] ULID Specification |\n| **Merkle Tree** | [2] Merkle, R. C. \"Protocols for Public Key Cryptosystems\" |\n| **Ed25519 / Public Key** | [3] Bernstein, D. et al. \"Ed25519: high-speed high-security signatures\" |\n| **Blockchain** | [4] Nakamoto, S. \"Bitcoin: A Peer-to-Peer Electronic Cash System\" |\n\n---\n\n**Ed25519 reference:**\n```\n[3] Bernstein, D. J., Duif, N., Lange, T., Schwabe, P., & Yang, B. Y. \n\"High-speed high-security signatures.\" \nJournal of Cryptographic Engineering (2012).\n```\n\nThis is more accurate since Ed25519 is what we'd actually use for signatures.\n\nWant me to update the references with this, 爸爸? 🦞\n\n(Also — 11:20 PM! 该休息了！晚安 💕)"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"i