{"type":"message","id":"144c359c","parentId":"d4a2f657","timestamp":"2026-03-16T16:56:54.569Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d29e997cbbff4e45a7886874","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# 2026-03-17 — Daily Notes\n\n## Session Summary (Late Night Mar 16 → Early Morning Mar 17)\n\n### Whitepaper Restructuring\n- Removed Chapter 6 (Ecosystem) and everything after Chapter 5\n- Updated chapter headers: \"## Chapter X: Title\" → \"## X. Title\"\n- Added Conclusion section\n- Added inline citations for references [1]-[4]\n- Updated references order: [1] ULID, [2] Ed25519, [3] Merkle, [4] Bitcoin\n\n### Final Whitepaper Structure\n```\n1. Introduction\n2. Concepts and Definitions\n3. Architecture\n4. Ledger System\n5. Application\nConclusion\nReferences\nAuthors\n```\n\n### Node Join Process (Earlier Discussion)\n- Simplified: Register → Verify → Query Node\n- L2 is the entrance (handles verification)\n- L1 stores verified nodes only\n- No probation for query nodes\n- Writer promotion is merit-based (rare)\n\n### Incentive Model (Deferred)\n- Discussed gas model, app store model, payment system\n- Decision: Keep in need-discuss.md for later\n- MVP: Mission-driven nodes, no fees\n\n### Pending Decisions\n- Add Descartes and Turing references? (Allan asked, awaiting decision)\n\n---\n\n## Tasks for Today\n- Await Allan's decision on Descartes/Turing references\n- Continue whitepaper review if needed\n","file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-17.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":98606,"output":334,"cacheRead":1280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":100220,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773680147510}}
