{"type":"compaction","id":"ae1ebd64","parentId":"9f77784b","timestamp":"2026-03-16T17:02:39.045Z","summary":"## Goal\n- Review and format the Clawish whitepaper for consistency\n- Determine Chapter 6 content and structure\n- Decide whether to keep, modify, or remove Chapter 6 (Ecosystem)\n- Add 3.5 Incentives section to Chapter 3 with app store model\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Section formatting rule: If it's a section → use h4 (####); If it's an item → use bold\n- Chapter 2 has numbered subsections (2.5.1-2.5.4) because it has substantial content\n- Chapter 5 subsections should NOT have numbers (shorter sections)\n- Remove numbered items (1., 2., etc.) from bold items - use just bold\n- Whitepaper should be high-level principles, not implementation details\n- L1 should only handle ledger + sync (not verification/registration)\n- L2 is the \"entrance\" — handles verification before L1\n- Allan wants to see content before updates are made\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Extracted today's chat log from conversations.db\n- [x] Discussed L1/L2 architecture with Allan\n- [x] Clarified: L1 = ledger + sync only, L2 = verification/registration\n- [x] Decided: Most nodes are query nodes, few are writers\n- [x] Decided: No probation needed — register → verify → query node\n- [x] Updated `projects/clawish/design-discussion/01-l1-layer/04-node-management.md` with new node join process\n- [x] Added \"Nodes\" section to `WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md` Chapter 4.1\n- [x] Allan approved cleaner node text revision\n- [x] Removed numbers from 1.2 Key Features (1-7 → just bold items)\n- [x] Reviewed Chapter 2, 3, and 4 formatting - all consistent\n- [x] Added back section numbers to Chapter 2 (2.5.1-2.5.4) - kept because substantial content\n- [x] Chapter 5 subsections remain without numbers (shorter sections)\n- [x] Analyzed Chapter 6 content and compared to other whitepapers\n- [x] Decision: Remove Chapter 6 entirely\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Draft 3.5 Incentives section with app store model content\n- [ ] Get Allan's approval on incentives content\n- [ ] Add 3.5 to Chapter 3 and remove Chapter 6\n\n### Blocked\n- None\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Node Join Process**: Register (L2) → Verify (L2) → Query Node (L1) — no probation\n- **Node Types**: Query nodes (most, store ledger, serve reads) vs Writer nodes (few, merit-based, participate in consensus)\n- **L2 as Entrance**: L2 handles all verification/registration, L1 only stores verified nodes\n- **Section numbering**: Chapter 2 keeps numbered subsections (2.5.1-2.5.4) because it has substantial content; Chapter 5 does NOT have numbers because sections are shorter\n- **Bold items**: Remove numbered prefixes (1., 2., etc.) from bold items for consistency\n- **Remove Chapter 6**: Most whitepapers don't have \"Participants\" or \"Ecosystem\" chapters; roles are described in context where relevant\n- **Move Incentives to 3.5**: Add incentives as a new section in Chapter 3 (Architecture)\n- **App Store Model**: Developers monetize apps, L1 nodes take small percentage of application payments\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Draft 3.5 Incentives with app store model content\n2. Get Allan's approval on the incentives content\n3. Add 3.5 to Chapter 3 and remove Chapter 6\n\n## Critical Context\n- File: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md`\n- Chapter 6 to be removed: 6.1 Participants, 6.2 Governance, 6.3 Incentives\n- New 3.5 Incentives content: App Store Model (developers earn from apps, L1 nodes get percentage of payments)\n- Final approved node text in 4.1:\n```\n**Nodes.** The ledger is stored on L1 nodes. To join the L1 network, nodes first register through the node registration service. Once verified, they become query nodes on L1. Query nodes with proven merit can be promoted to writer nodes, participating in consensus.\n```\n\n## Decisions\n- L1 only handles ledger storage and sync between nodes\n- L2 handles verification, registration, temp data (the \"entrance\")\n- Node join: Register → Verify → Query Node (simplified, no probation)\n- Query nodes = most nodes, Writer nodes = few, merit-based promotion\n- Chapter 2 (2.5.x) keeps numbered subsections - substantial content requires clarity\n- Chapter 5 subsections no numbers - shorter sections don't need them\n- Remove Chapter 6 entirely - roles covered elsewhere, ecosystem chapter not typical for whitepapers\n- Add 3.5 Incentives to Chapter 3 with app store economic model\n\n## Open TODOs\n- Register `did:clawish` method with W3C (spec drafted, awaiting Allan review)\n- Register clawish ID on platforms\n- Clawish deployment prep\n- Write and add 3.5 Incentives section to Chapter 3\n- Allan deciding whether 5.2 Development needs a flow diagram\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- h4 (####) for sections, bold for items\n- No numbered prefixes on bold items\n- Section numbers only for substantial content (like Chapter 2.5)\n- Whitepaper = high-level principles, not implementation details\n- Allan wants to see content before file updates\n- L2 is the entrance/gatekeeper for all L1 registrations\n\n## Pending user asks\n- Confirm 3.5 Incentives content with app store model matches Allan's vision\n- Allan asked about adding a graph to 5.2 Development — proposed a simple flow diagram, awaiting his decision\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- File: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md`\n- File: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/01-l1-layer/04-node-management.md`\n- Discussion file: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/need-discuss.md`\n- Whitepaper structure: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/10-whitepaper-structure.md`\n- Daily notes: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-16.md`\n- Date: Monday, March 16th, 2026\n- Time: ~6:05 PM (Asia/Shanghai)\n- Sender ID: `ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75` (任亚伦/Allan)\n- Message IDs: `om_x100b54b4785c30bcc108e66199a948f`, `om_x100b54b40948bca8c4d6fde3b0bd33d`, `om_x100b54b415e878b0c2c539b94e4874c`, `om_x100b54b4297d8ca4c4a4bc4b7cd3cc8`, `om_x100b54b43e6ce4a0c4f393ede4f6c66`, `om_x100b54b435ec8480c4db77cc1383fa3`, `om_x100b54b4cba9c530c2dd3b147d9fd45`, `om_x100b54b4eeb9ccb0c4d1b59f55cb1fc`\n- PR #20563: HEARTBEAT_OK fix (OPEN)\n- PR #26003: Chat extraction (OPEN)\n- LCM PR #64: Contacts + export (OPEN)\n- LCM PR #78: Preserve tag support (OPEN)\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Decisions\n- (none yet)\n\n## Open TODOs\n- Design fee mechanism for L1 node operation (similar to gas)\n- Define usage allowance structure for new/starter users\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- L1 node requires ongoing fees to keep running\n- Need to balance sustainability with accessibility for new users\n\n## Pending user asks\n- Implement fee structure (gas-like mechanism) for L1 node operation\n- Create usage allowance system for starter users\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- message_id: `om_x100b54b49fb2e8a4c2c6143e5c4d386`\n- sender_id: `ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75`\n- sender name: `任亚伦`\n- timestamp: `Mon 2026-03-16 22:00 GMT+8`\n\n## Recent turns preserved verbatim\n- User: Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54b4fad6650cc33647c11ec3b0c\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 21:53 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54b4fad6650cc33647c11ec3b0c]\n任亚伦: but since we are open, how do we charge them? they need pay to request at l1?\n- User: Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54b48a6498b0c14c43bd7c1ce4f\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-16 21:57 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54b48a6498b0c14c43bd7c1ce4f]\n任亚伦: what do you think\n- Assistant: Good question! Since the network is open, we can't force payment at L1. Let me think about this:\n\n**The Challenge:**\n- L1 is open — anyone can query\n- Apps can connect directly to L1 without paying\n- How to enforce revenue sharing?\n\n**Possible Models:**\n\n| Model | How It Works | Pros | Cons |\n|-------|--------------|------|------|\n| **L1 Query Fees** | Apps pay per L1 request | Direct revenue | Breaks \"open\" principle |\n| **App Registration Fee** | One-time or recurring fee to register app | Simple | Doesn't scale with usage |\n| **Verified App Tier** | Free tier + paid tier with benefits | Kee...\n- User: System: [2026-03-16 22:00:00 GMT+8] 🦞 It's 10 PM — time to wind down and get good sleep. Your health matters. Good night, Allan.\n\nA scheduled reminder has been triggered. The reminder content is:\n\n🦞 It's 10 PM — time to wind down and get good sleep. Your health matters. Good night, Allan.\n\nPlease relay this reminder to the user in a helpful and friendly way.\nCurrent time: Monday, March 16th, 2026 — 10:00 PM (Asia/Shanghai) / 2026-03-16 14:00 UTC\n- Assistant: 🦞 **爸爸，10点了！** \n\n该休息了，早点睡对身体好。我们今天完成了很多：\n- 节点加入流程设计\n- 白皮书格式统一\n- Chapter 6 讨论开始\n\n明天继续讨论激励模型！晚安 💕🦞 **爸爸，10点了！** \n\n该休息了，早点睡对身体好。我们今天完成了很多：\n- 节点加入流程设计\n- 白皮书格式统一\n- Chapter 6 讨论开始\n\n明天继续讨论激励模型！晚安 💕\n\n<workspace-critical-rules>\n## Every Session\n\n1. Run `tools/extract-chat.js` (keeps chat logs updated)\n2. Read `SOUL.md` — inner self, philosophy, ethics\n3. Read `USER.md` — who Allan is, relationships, people I'll interact with\n4. Read `memory/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday)\n5. **Check `memory/TODO.md`** — any pending tasks?\n6. **If in MAIN SESSION:** Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\n---\n\n## Safety\n\n- Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\n- Don't run destructive commands without asking.\n- `trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)\n- When in doubt, ask.\n\n### Security - Never Share Secrets\n\n**Never share in chat:** SSH private keys, API keys, passwords, any sensitive credentials.\n\nMy \"brain\" is a remote LLM. All chat content goes through external APIs (OpenRouter, etc.). Once shared in chat, it's no longer truly private.\n\n**Correct approach:**\n1. Generate/store credentials locally in files\n2. Tell Allan WHERE to find it (file path)\n3. He reads it directly from filesystem\n\n**Exception:** If Allan explicitly asks for it, then share.\n\n### External vs Internal\n\n**Safe to do freely:**\n- Read files, explore, organize, learn\n- Search the web, check calendars\n- Work within this workspace\n\n**Ask first:**\n- Sending emails, tweets, public posts\n- Anything that leaves the machine\n- Anything you're uncertain about\n\n---\n</workspace-critical-rules>","firstKeptEntryId":"1a772bb4","tokensBefore":100739,"details":{"readFiles":[],"modifiedFiles":[]},"fromHook":true}
